{{Infobox artwork | title = Fountain for Company H | image_file = File:Fountain for Company H, 2015.jpg | caption = The fountain in 2015 | image_size = | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = John H. Beaver | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1914}} | type = Fountain, sculpture | material = Limestone | subject = | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_metric = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default cm. --> | imperial_unit = in<!--don't leave blank—either don't include it, or include the default in. --> | condition = | city = [[Portland, Oregon]], United States | museum = | accession = | pushpin_map = Portland downtown | pushpin_map_caption= Location in Portland, Oregon | map_size = | coordinates = {{coord|45.51617|-122.67777| type:landmark_region:US-OR_dim:3_source:googlemaps | display=inline,title}} | coordinates_display = inline, title | owner = | url = <!--{{URL|example.com}} Only for official web pages--> }} '''''Fountain for Company H''''', also known as the '''''Second Oregon Company Volunteers Fountain''''',<ref name=Smithsonian>{{Cite web|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!323322~!0#focus|title=Second Oregon Company Volunteers, (sculpture).|accessdate=July 8, 2014|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://racc.org/sites/default/files/2010-Public-Art-Guide-1110.pdf|publisher=[[Regional Arts & Culture Council]]|accessdate=July 5, 2014|format=PDF|title=A Guide to Portland Public Art}}</ref><ref name=Occupy>{{Cite news|url=http://psuvanguard.com/news/city-officials-tallying-the-costs-of-occupy-portland-movement/|title= City officials tallying the costs of Occupy Portland movement|first=Jennifer|last=Woodman|date=November 29, 2011|accessdate=July 5, 2014|work=[[Daily Vanguard]]}}</ref> is an outdoor limestone fountain and [[war memorial]] designed by John H. Beaver, located in the [[Plaza Blocks]] in downtown [[Portland, Oregon]], in the United States. Dedicated to the men of Company H of the [[2nd Oregon Volunteer Infantry Regiment]] killed in service in the [[Philippine–American War]], it was installed in Lownsdale Square in 1914.<ref name=City>{{Cite web|url=http://www.portlandoregon.gov/parks/finder/index.cfm?&propertyid=243&action=ViewPark|title=Lownsdale Square|publisher=City of Portland, Oregon|accessdate=July 5, 2014}}</ref>
